dct_title_s: Petri Kaerii Germania Inferior, id est XVII provinciarum ejus novae et exactae tabulae geographicae
dct_alternative_sm: Petri Kaerii Germania Inferior, id est 17 provinciarum ejus novae et exactae tabulae geographicae
Germania Inferior, id est XVII provinciarum ejus novae et exactae tabulae geographicae, cum luculentis singularum
dct_description_sm: cum luculentis singularum descriptionibus additis Ã  Petro Montano.

Engraved maps of the Low Countries and regions (Belgium, Holland, Luxember, Artois). Includes Leo Belgicus, historical maps, elaborate cartouches, topographical details, manners and costumes of inhabitants, town views, and ships.
Engraved t.p. includes arch flanked by coats of arms, surmounted by queen figure and "Jehovah" in Hebrew, with lion, ship, sailors, book, compass, figures at bottom and skull clock.
Last page inlcudes Latin statement mentioning atlases of De Jode, Mercator & Ortelius with pulication statement below.
2nd ed.; text reset, plates reprinted; map of East Frisia mentioned twice in Index.
